rent-last for just `TaskAdapter`? I will need a cast if I create a child loader that focuses exclusively on `TaskAdapter` while delegating others to the parent. I wonder about the implications for class loading and casting issues, especially with `Project`. Would reflection be necessary?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring a helper class solution**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a helper class loaded in the child that would use standard Java calls to `TaskAdapter`, possibly with a main or static method. From the parent, I could call this helper via reflection or maybe an interface. I can define the helper in test sources implementing a parent interface. If the helper implements `Runnable`, I can cast it if the child delegates `java.lang.Runnable` to the parent. I could make `IsolatedTaskAdapterExercise` a public static final class in the test jar.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KBfaxz7C56SeknrnWrJSp2jS|fc_03f19f5e1c5d66c80169fbbe662b888196bd9fcba9326953da", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|URLClassLoader\" tests/src -g'*.java' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4993, "output": 3330, "cacheRead": 16384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24707, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778105899722, "responseId": "resp_03f19f5e1c5d66c80169fbbe2c68e081968473e0cac157a3df"}}
