HXm5f6SG-PBoqyGYkdyfBTt5WRSFcC21dL6jpX_DrUDmcjeA4gDOT14nTwIJTlfnt27jShMHJszTJm7ahLfREGLmVcxgejrKVmU7XW7MEYDnqkGprTldvWI9mOyo98Fqj_zCfel1gsM3eQDWbihPOF93MwdiDdIYR4tUK59TYSV91saWWvNVu6lvUOQLkRKoYh0CAM2cDohR2C8UGmftYolcrQB9vUrhmwk0kB7piHZXHWzegwEDUTB-GZ-ULWgSqjHrlSAUC21_tDgAPWyEExeYoeOJUzGqvMCanQkITalSdncoVoZxsGBgu46eZgzicqoLHxi-YFLVV14S0vvJ3tpmSKhfA0F74-Do5oWtPl468RENR_FwLoHg2_pXgTU_iEq_vtjNDzyVWmkW7PQYu1AWJwF0hK8M0AFDhrtFfOj6cuCmQ2jXre1C9SmsK-pCNipY9Fl_IpFpByvxyC\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test order issues**\\n\\nI'm considering avoiding certain tests and thinking about adapting the test to run first. JUnit doesn't enforce order, which can be a problem if earlier tests affect class fields. \\n\\nI noticed that there was no TaskAdapter test before, so it's likely that the TaskAdapter’s `checkTaskClass(ProxyTask.class, project)` method didn't call the Project class. It calls a check before execution, expecting the field to be null. \\n\\nIt’s puzzling that it's not covered. Perhaps the native-image build initializes the TaskAdapter class at build time? I need to investigate if there's a static initializer.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating method execution**\\n\\nI’m trying to understand why the class methods are parsed with descriptors, but the parameter class isn't loaded. Maybe the line class$ comes before c.getMethod, which could be an issue since resolving checkTaskClass isn't enough if the Project is already loaded. I wonder if I should remove checkTaskClass from the same test. Alternatively, I could create a separate test called \\\"executesProxyWithoutConfiguredProject\\\" that doesn’t call checkTaskClass or instantiate the Project.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading strategies**\\n\\nI'm considering if I could load `TaskAdapter` from an Ant jar in a child-first loader. It implements `TypeAdapter`, which is loaded by the child. What if I configure the loader to be parent-last for just `TaskAdapter`? I will need a cast if I create a child loader that focuses exclusively on `TaskAdapter` while delegating others to the parent. I wonder about the implications for class loading and casting issues, especially with `Project`. Would reflection be necessary?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring a helper class solution**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a helper class loaded in the child that would use standard Java calls to `TaskAdapter`, possibly with a main or static method. From the parent, I could call this helper via reflection or maybe an interface. I can define the helper in test sources implementing a parent interface. If the helper implements `Runnable`, I can cast it if the child delegates `java.lang.Runnable` to the parent. I could make `IsolatedTaskAdapterExercise` a public static final class in the test jar.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KBfaxz7C56SeknrnWrJSp2jS|fc_03f19f5e1c5d66c80169fbbe662b888196bd9fcba9326953da", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|URLClassLoader\" tests/src -g'*.java' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4993, "output": 3330, "cacheRead": 16384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24707, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778105899722, "responseId": "resp_03f19f5e1c5d66c80169fbbe2c68e081968473e0cac157a3df"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_KBfaxz7C56SeknrnWrJSp2jS|fc_03f19f5e1c5d66c80169fbbe662b888196bd9fcba9326953da", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-protobuf_3_7/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_protobuf_3_7/DescriptorsInnerFileDescriptorTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-sha